We recommended the following:

a.) The BAC strictly follows the procedure of procurement prescribed by the Revised IRR of RA 9184 by making sure that Requests for Quotation are sent to prospect suppliers before any award of contract;

b.) Recommend award of contract only to suppliers with valid PhilGEPS Registration;

c.) Ensure posting of the Notice of Award, Contract or Purchase Order and the Notice to Proceed in the case of negotiated procurement- lease of venue; and

d.) The absent personnel to explain in writing the reason of their absence and if warranted, refund the amount expended for their food and accommodation.

We recommended the following:
The BAC strictly follows the procedure of procurement prescribed by the Revised IRR of RA 9184 by making sure that Requests for Quotation are sent to prospect suppliers before any award of contract;
Recommend award of contract only to suppliers with valid PhilGEPS Registration;
Ensure posting of the Notice of Award, Contract or Purchase Order and the Notice to Proceed in the case of negotiated procurement- lease of venue; and
The absent personnel to explain in writing the reason of their absence and if warranted, refund the amount expended for their food and accommodation.

We recommended that the management:

The Bids and Awards Committee properly analyze the procurement of materials and labor when construction is implemented by administration. Construction projects implemented by Administration wherein materials and labor are source from different suppliers should have separate PRs according to the nature of the items and post in the Invitation to Bid the items contained in the PR and prepare Purchase Orders base on the PR;

Properly post the Invitation to Bid in PhilGEPS under Classification/Project Category;

Post in Philgeps the Notice of Award and Notice to Proceed in procurements done thru Alternative Method under small value procurement and attach the proof of posting in the DVs; and prepare the recommendation to the LCE in the award of contract in favor of the supplier with the Lowest Calculated and Responsive Quotation in all its procurement thru Negotiated Method;

The Municipal Engineer to indicate the date in the Project Accomplishment Reports and inspect and certify 100% completion of Pakyaw before any payment is made; and 

The Municipal Accountant to:

Ensure that supporting documents for procurement are complete, particularly the proof of Posting the Notice of Award and Notice to Proceed in the PhilGPES, the certification by the Municipal Engineer for 100% completion in the Project Accomplishment Reports for payment of Pakyaw labor, and the Charge Sales Invoice as Principal evidence in the procurement of goods on account; and

Properly analyze the transactions in the construction projects to properly record the accounts and to make necessary adjustments of the accounts affected.

